<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-138-016 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 951 682</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer  June 1991 v24 n6 p92(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tex typesetting with a difference. (Micro Press Inc.'s Vector Texdesktop publishing software, Pxlgen and New Fase computer fonts,and K-Talk Communications Inc.'s Publishing Companion) (SoftwareReview) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pappas, T. L.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MicroPress Inc's Vector Tex, $299, is implementation software forTeX, the powerful typesetting program.andP;  TeX documents areformatted in a 'mark-up' language and a separate driver program isneeded to view or print the document.andP;  Vector Tex, usuallyreferred to as Vtex, provides the standard set of macros that TeXuses as well as a previewer and several printer drivers includingPostscript, HP Laser Jet-compatibles and dot matrix printers.andO;Vtex uses scalable vector fonts rather than raster fonts.andP;  Anotherprogram called Pxlgen, $100, also from MicroPress, converts theVtex vector fonts to raster fonts.andP;  One especially helpful featureof Vtex is the ease with which graphics files from PC Paintbrushand MacPaint are handled.andP;  There are two packages available forWordPerfect users for Vtex.andP;  MicroPress' New Fase, $99, generatesfonts for WordPerfect.andP;  K-Talk Communications Inc's PublishingCompanion is a WYSIWYG front-end in which the user can writeWordPerfect documents that are then generated into TeX or Latexfiles.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MicroPress Inc. (Products)K-Talk Communications Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   TeX (Desktop publishing software) (Computer programs)Vector Tex (Desktop publishing software)Publishing Companion (Desktop publishing software)Pxlgen (Computer font)New Fase (Computer font).andO;Topic:     Desktop PublishingAdd-In/On SoftwareFontsSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>